Business Brief -- MIP Properties Inc.:
   REIT Says Security Pacific
   Calls $28.9 Million of Debt
"The company has been unable to maintain compliance with
the net worth covenant under the credit agreement and, as a
result, the bank has elected to declare the default and
accelerate the loan," said Carl C. Gregory III, chairman and
chief executive officer of MIP, a real estate investment
trust. For the first nine months of last year, MIP had a loss
of $22 million, or $2.44 a share, compared with net income of
$2 million, or 22 cents a share, a year earlier.